parameters: Godrays
Actor4
\p3Hurry up, \N[1]. I know you've got
it the worst with that heavy armor of
yours, but we're almost out of the
desert. Telluria Field is just ahead!
Telluria1
\willHey, \N[1]! Hold on a second!
A
CAM EVENT 1 1600
Telluria1
\willHuff... puff... looks like I
barely caught you four in time.
Telluria1
\willOr... I guess just you. Before you
catch up to the others, I need to
tell you something important.
Telluria1
\willThe magic forge in my shop... that's not the
only one in the Overworld. Another one rests within
the Smithery in Telluria Castle Town.
Telluria1
\willThe flame in Telluria Castle Town's
magic forge burns much brighter than
Bladesville's. You'll be able to craft
some incredibly powerful equipment!
Telluria1
\will...
Telluria1
\willOh, you wonder why I guard the weaker forge?
Telluria1
\willWell... the keeper of Telluria Castle Town's
magic forge is a lifelong blacksmith with close
ties to my family. I'd trust him with my life.
He's not very talkative, but he's very skilled.
Telluria1
\willAnd besides, Bladesville has been my family's
home for more generations than you can count. I
guide travelers, sometimes advise the Town Master,
maintain the ancient history of the Blazing Sands...
Telluria1
\willMy services are more needed in Bladesville.
But hey, don't be afraid to stop by at my
shop again and say hi.
Telluria1
\willI've still got a lot for you to do,
after all. Of course, your main goal
should be defeating \c[18]Apocalypse\c[0]... but
your help would be greatly appreciated.
Telluria1
\willMy apologies for rambling a bit. You
should catch up to your friends now.
Telluria1
\willIt was good to have you in the Blazing
Sands, \N[1]. Best of luck in Telluria
Field and wherever you go afterwards.
